cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.CL 

The paper discusses the impact of non-elite journals on scholarly research, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely category as it deals with the organization and dissemination of scholarly information. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as it deals with finding and accessing relevant information. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are relevant as they involve the analysis and dissemination of information. Finally, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is relevant as it deals with natural language processing, which is important for understanding and analyzing scholarly articles.
